Preliminary notes: 

The programme must be developed in the C language. 
The use of global variables is completely forbidden. 
The use of functions is favoured.
Comment the code whenever important. 

1. Description of the problem
The aim is to develop a programme to manage the assessments of the trainees in a module.
Using a vector to store the data, the programme should provide the user with the following options 
options:

- Record values (grades)
- Check the recorded values (grades)
- Set all values to zero
- Consult the average marks for the UFCD
- Check wanted negative marks and who owns them
- Check the positive marks and who owns them


Tip: 
Use the id of the vector to identify the learner. 
For example, trainee number N could be registered under id (N - 1).
